# Firebase Admin (server-side session + Firestore writes)
#
# If Console shows "Key creation is not allowed" (org policy), do NOT use a JSON key.
# Local dev: install Google Cloud SDK, then run:
#   gcloud auth application-default login --project ring-test-manager
# Leave the three variables below EMPTY — Admin SDK uses Application Default Credentials.
#
# Option A: paste full JSON (only if you already have a key from before the policy)
# FIREBASE_SERVICE_ACCOUNT_JSON={"type":"service_account",...}
# Option B: separate fields (same — only if you have an existing key)
